%md
## Time Series Forecasting (FireTS)

%pyspark
sc.addFile("hdfs://big0.iie.org.mx:9000/JSGP/datasets/london/utils/fireTS/core.py")
sc.addFile("hdfs://big0.iie.org.mx:9000/JSGP/datasets/london/utils/fireTS/utils.py")
sc.addFile("hdfs://big0.iie.org.mx:9000/JSGP/datasets/london/utils/fireTS/models.py")

import utils
import core
import models
from models import NARX, DirectAutoRegressor
import pandas as pd
import os
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import re
import matplotlib.dates as mdates
from pyspark.ml.evaluation import RegressionEvaluator

%pyspark
# Select forecast method: 1 for meter, 2 for category
forecast=1

#Select meter to forecast
meter="MAC000003"

#Select category to forecast
category=2

# Number of experiments to run
n_exp=2

# Percentaje of data used to train
perc=0.80

%pyspark

#Read data

if (forecast==1):
    #From dataframe generated at analytics_data notebook
    data0=meter_weather_1h.filter(col("METER_ID")==meter)
    data1=data0.toPandas()
    data = data1.set_index('TIMESTAMP')
    data.index = pd.to_datetime(data.index)
    data=data.sort_values(by=['METER_ID', "TIMESTAMP"])
    porc_train=int(perc*len(data))
    ytrain = data['ENERGY'].iloc[:porc_train]
    Xtrain = data.loc[:, ['TEMPERATURE', "HD"]].iloc[:porc_train, :]

    ytest = data['ENERGY'].iloc[porc_train:-1]
    Xtest = data.loc[:, ['TEMPERATURE', "HD"]].iloc[porc_train:-1, :]
    
else:
    
    data0=cat_weather_1h.filter(col("CAT")==category)
    data1=data0.toPandas()
    data = data1.set_index('TIMESTAMP')
    data.index = pd.to_datetime(data.index)
    data=data.sort_values(by=['CAT', "TIMESTAMP"])
    porc_train=int(perc*len(data))
    #can be e_sum or e_avg
    ytrain = data['e_sum'].iloc[:porc_train]
    Xtrain = data.loc[:, ['TEMPERATURE', "HD"]].iloc[:porc_train, :]

    ytest = data['ENERGY'].iloc[porc_train:-1]
    Xtest = data.loc[:, ['TEMPERATURE', "HD"]].iloc[porc_train:-1, :]

%pyspark
print(Xtrain)

%md
#### NARX with Random Forest and grid seach for hyperparameter tuning

msg.data: NARX with Random Forest and grid seach for hyperparameter tuning

paragraphs.text:
%pyspark


r2_win_narx=0
model_win_narx=NARX(RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=15), auto_order=24, exog_order=[1,1], exog_delay=[1,1])

for i in range(n_exp):
    
    narx_mdl = NARX(RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=15), auto_order=24, exog_order=[1,1], exog_delay=[1,1])
    para_grid = {'n_estimators': [1, 5, 10, 20, 30, 50]}
    narx_mdl.grid_search(Xtrain, ytrain, para_grid, verbose=1)
    narx_mdl.fit(Xtrain, ytrain)
    ypred = narx_mdl.predict(Xtest, ytest, step=1)
    ypred = pd.Series(ypred, index=ytest.index)

    results=pd.DataFrame({'TIMESTAMP':ypred.index, 'prediction':ypred.values, 'label':ytest.values})
    results_df=spark.createDataFrame(results)  
    results_df=results_df.filter(~(isnan(results_df["prediction"])))
    evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="r2")
    r2 = evaluator.evaluate(results_df)
    print("Run %d - R2 = %f" % (i, r2))
    
    if r2>r2_win_narx:
        r2_win_narx=r2
        model_win_narx=narx_mdl
        y_pred_win=ypred
        winner_exp=i
        results_win_narx=results
        results_win_narx_df=results_df

print("\nBest model found at experiment %d\n" %winner_exp)
evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="rmse")
rmse = evaluator.evaluate(results_win_narx_df)
print("Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE) on test data = %g" % rmse)

evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="mse")
mse = evaluator.evaluate(results_win_narx_df)
print("Mean Squared Error (MSE) on test data = %g" % mse)

evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="mae")
mae = evaluator.evaluate(results_win_narx_df)
print("Mean Absolute Error (MAE) on test data = %g" % mae)

evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="r2")
r2 = evaluator.evaluate(results_win_narx_df)
print("R2 coefficient (R2) on test data = %g" % r2)

#### NARX with Lasso

%pyspark
from sklearn.linear_model import Lasso

narx_mdl = NARX(Lasso(), auto_order=24, exog_order=[1,1], exog_delay=[1,1])
narx_mdl.fit(Xtrain, ytrain)
ypred = narx_mdl.predict(Xtest, ytest, step=1)
ypred = pd.Series(ypred, index=ytest.index)

from pyspark.ml.evaluation import RegressionEvaluator
results=pd.DataFrame({'TIMESTAMP':ypred.index, 'prediction':ypred.values, 'label':ytest.values})
results_df=spark.createDataFrame(results)  
results_df=results_df.filter(~(isnan(results_df["prediction"])))
evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="rmse")
rmse = evaluator.evaluate(results_df)
print("Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE) on test data = %g" % rmse)

evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="mse")

print("Mean Squared Error (MSE) on test data = %g" % mse)

evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="mae")

print("Mean Absolute Error (MAE) on test data = %g" % mae)

evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="r2")

## Plot Results

%pyspark
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.dates as mdates

#Choose results to plot
plt_results=results_win_narx.iloc[0:200,:]

results_graph=plt_results.sort_values(by=['TIMESTAMP'])
results_graph['mdate'] = [mdates.date2num(d) for d in results_graph["TIMESTAMP"]]

plt.close('all') 
fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize = (20,10))
ax1.plot( results_graph['mdate'],results_graph['label'],marker='.', color='skyblue', linewidth=2, label='Actual Data');
ax1.plot( results_graph['mdate'],results_graph['prediction'],marker='.', color='olive', linewidth=2, label='Predicted data')
ax1.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M'))
plt.legend()
plt.xticks(rotation=60)
plt.show()
